<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-12">
  <h1 class="mb-2 text-3xl font-bold">Data Deletion Request</h1>
  <p class="mb-8 text-sm text-black/40">Your right to be forgotten</p>

  <div class="space-y-6 text-black/70">

    <div class="rounded-lg border border-black/10 bg-white p-6">
      <h2 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-ink">What data we hold</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-sm">
        <li>Your email address and hashed password</li>
        <li>OAuth access tokens for connected social media accounts</li>
        <li>Media files (images and videos) you uploaded</li>
        <li>Post history and captions</li>
        <li>Session data</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-lg border border-black/10 bg-white p-6">
      <h2 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-ink">How to delete your data</h2>
      <p class="mb-4 text-sm">To request complete deletion of all your data from SocialPost, send an email to:</p>
      <a href="mailto:contact@urlyapp.com?subject=Data%20Deletion%20Request"
         class="inline-block rounded-lg bg-mint px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-white hover:bg-mint/90">
        contact@urlyapp.com
      </a>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm">Include your registered email address in the request. We will delete all associated data within 30 days and send a confirmation.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-lg border border-black/10 bg-white p-6">
      <h2 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-ink">Revoking platform access</h2>
      <p class="mb-3 text-sm">You can also revoke SocialPost's access to each platform directly:</p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
        <li>
          <strong>Facebook / Instagram:</strong>
          Settings → Security → Apps and Websites → Remove "SocialPost"
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>YouTube / Google:</strong>
          <a href="https://myaccount.google.com/permissions" class="text-mint underline" target="_blank">myaccount.google.com/permissions</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>TikTok:</strong>
          Profile → Settings → Apps and Permissions → Manage app permissions
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Pinterest:</strong>
          Settings → Security → Connected apps
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <p class="text-sm">
      For more information, see our <a href="/privacy" class="text-mint underline">Privacy Policy</a>.
    </p>

  </div>
</div>
